title: Watch: Portland Timbers' Darlington Nagbe scores two first-half goals against Colorado Rapids
text:
Portland Timbers midfielder Darlington Nagbe found his scoring touch on Sunday, with two goals in the first half against the Colorado Rapids at Providence Park.
Nagbe scored in the fifth minute on a free kick that blasted past Colorado goalkeeper Zac McMath to give the Timbers a 1-0 lead.
Nagbe followed that with a goal in the 33rd minute, heading in a deft pass from Lucas Melano, going far post, already behind McMath.
For Nagbe, it's his first two-goal game, or brace, for the season, his fourth and fifth goals in 2015.
